  <scopecontent id="aspace_e9bf4aeac1c517652a6563890f570842">
    <head>COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
<p>Artwork on deposit from the Lab of Ornithology. Includes works by George Miksch Sutton, Anna Botsford Comstock, John Gould, and others.</p><p>The John James Audubon, Louis Agassiz Fuertes and John Gould art work on deposit for the Lab has been added to the illustrators' corresponding collections.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_f16621daf5b0ac3e2e9ad865aba00880">
    <head>RELATED MATERIAL</head>
<p>The <extref xlink:href="http://resolver.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/EADresolver?id=RMM06721"> John James Audubon artwork, #6721</extref>, the <extref xlink:href="http://resolver.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/EADresolver?id=RMM02662">Louis Agassiz Fuertes papers, #2662 </extref>, and the <extref xlink:href="http://resolver.library.cornell.edu/cgi-bin/EADresolver?id=RMM04736"> John Gould Artwork Collection, #4736 </extref> also contain materials on deposit from the Laboratory of Ornithology
The digital collection can be viewed here <extref xlink:href="https://newcatalog.library.cornell.edu/catalog/6280355">https://newcatalog.library.cornell.edu/catalog/6280355</extref>. Note that not all items in the digital collection have been placed on deposit in the physical collection within the University Archives, a number of items remain on display at the Laboratory of Ornithology.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <odd id="aspace_d59d969864d1651501275417bc2a4919">
    <head>General</head>
<p>Items with four digit numbers can be identified using the <extref xlink:href="https://newcatalog.library.cornell.edu/catalog/6280355">Lab of Ornithology art database.</extref></p>  </odd>
